author: newsroom@capegazette.com (Dan Cook)
title: Cape volleyball defeats solid St. Thomas More squad 3-1
text:
Cape volleyball defeats solid St. Thomas More squad 3-1 Vikings improve to 10-1 on the season By Dan Cook | Oct 16, 2015 Photo by: Dan Cook The Cape squad leaps with joy after the final kill shot of the 3-1 win over St. Thomas More. 
The Lady Vikings volleyball squad came out of the locker room on fire to win their 10th match of the season with a 25-16, 26-24, 12-25 and 25-22 victory over St. Thomas More Academy. 
Sophomore setter Logan Shuttleworth assisted on 35 points while senior libero Kira Vitella made 28 digs in the match. Middle blocker Abby E'Nama slammed eight kills, Taylor Collier picked up seven and Alison Palmer and Izzie Marsico each had six kills. 
"I was thrilled with our first set performance," said head coach Tyler Coupe. "I think it was the best we've played all season. We knew St. Thomas More was going to be a strong team from the get go. They pushed us and we responded." 
Coupe was quick to praise his players for the way they responded to playing a very tough Ravens squad. 
"Kira Vitella, by far, had the best game of her season," he said. "She kept us in every single point. Whenever we were down, I knew she would get a great up for us. She had an amazing night." 
"We really came out and played together and strong," said Vitella, giving kudos to her teammates. 
Offensively, Abby E'Nama and Taylor Collier led the way for the Lady Vikings. 
"As a team, we were plagued by errors," Coupe said. "But Abby and Taylor keep their heads level and pushed us through." 
"I finally got my approach down," said Collier. " I started to get my swing and just had my focus and was getting all my serves in. I thought it was important to get the team together to bring us up because this is always a tough game for us, and we just need to be together when we're playing." 
Cape has never won more than 11 games in a season. They are 10-1 under first-year coach Coupe with four matches left to play. 
The Lady Vikings junior varsity defeated the Ravens JV 2-1 to move their record to 7-4 on the season. 
The Vikings travel to Delmar Tuesday, Oct. 20 for a match up with the 6-4 Wildcats. Cape senior captain Kira Vitella serves one of her two aces in the contest.
